randoop.operation

Class ConcreteOperation

  • java.lang.Object
    • randoop.operation.TypedOperation<CallableOperation>
      • randoop.operation.ConcreteOperation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Operation>, Operation

    public class ConcreteOperation
extends TypedOperation<CallableOperation>
    ConcreteOperation is an abstract implementation of Operation that represents the operations that can occur within a test. A concrete operation is either defined in a non-generic context, or is instantiated from a GenericOperation.

      • toParseableString

        public java.lang.String toParseableString()
        Returns a string representation of this Operation, which can be read by static parse method for class. For a class C implementing the Operation interface, this method should return a String s such that parsing the string returns an object equivalent to this object, i.e. C.parse(this.s).equals(this).
        Returns:
        string descriptor of Operation object.
